title: Flight Simulator 2020 - POI - New Zealand - Waitangi Treaty grounds
description:
In this video we will fly over the Waitangi Treaty grounds. The Treaty of Waitangi (MƒÅori: Te Tiriti o Waitangi) is a document of central importance to the history, to the political constitution of the state, and to the national mythos of New Zealand. It has played a major role in the treatment of the MƒÅori population in New Zealand, by successive governments and the wider population, a role that has been especially prominent from the late 20th century. The treaty document is an agreement, not a treaty as recognized in international law and it has no independent legal status, being legally effective only to the extent it is recognized in various statutes. It was first signed on 6 February 1840 by Captain William Hobson as consul for the British Crown and by MƒÅori chiefs (rangatira) from the North Island of New Zealand.
